ax  itself)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-rose-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-rose_7-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Rose, Joel (2001). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=8jXmbJRuPY4C&amp;printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>New York Sawed in Half: An Urban Historical</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Bloomsbury_Publishing\" title=\"Bloomsbury Publishing\">Bloomsbury Publishing</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-58234-098-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1-58234-098-6\">1-58234-098-6</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=New+York+Sawed+in+Half%3A+An+Urban+Historical&amp;rft.pub=Bloomsbury+Publishing&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.isbn=1-58234-098-6&amp;rft.au=Rose%2C+Joel&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D8jXmbJRuPY4C%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASawing-off+of+Manhattan+Island\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sawing-off_of_Manhattan_Island&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Further reading\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20070927202443/http://www.historybuff.com/library/refmanhattan.html\">\"The Day They Almost Sawed Off Manhattan\"</a>. <i>History Buff</i>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" h